During a Cabinet meeting, President Trump discussed various topics including the possibility of a 4th of July parade, the state of the economy, trade deals with China, the border wall, and his disapproval of Representative Ilhan Omar's remarks. He expressed dissatisfaction with the proposed border deal from Congress and hinted at the possibility of declaring a national emergency to build the wall. He also mentioned the ongoing trade negotiations with China and the need for a real deal. President Trump emphasized his commitment to building the wall and protecting the country from illegal immigration and drugs.